{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"source": "https://minecraft.fandom.com/fr/wiki/Structures", "section": "Structures retir\u00e9s", "file_origin": "files/Structures.txt"}, "page_content": "Ce sont des structures qui ont \u00e9t\u00e9 supprim\u00e9es ou qui n'existent que dans les anciennes versions de Minecraft .\n- Structure : Pyramide de briques | Biome(s) : Anywhere, since biomes didn't exist back then. | Description : A giant pyramid that had no interior and was made solely out of bricks. The official name for this structure is unknown. Was removed in Java Edition Infdev 20100327 .\n- Structure : Terres lointaines | Biome(s) : Around the World boundary . | Description : A glitch appearing from many of the older Java versions, although the most well-known version is from Java Edition Version Beta 1.7.3 . The glitch is a result of the Perlin noise generators that Minecraft uses breaking at a distance of 12,550,812 blocks on the X or Z axis. This structure was removed in Java Edition Beta 1.8 from a bugfix.\n- Structure : Pilier de verre | Biome(s) : Any Overworld biome. | Description : A tall, one-by-one glass pillar which stretched from the end portal room in the stronghold all the way to the build limit. According to Jeb, it was a debug feature that he forgot to remove. It was soon removed in the version Java Edition Beta 1.9 Prerelease 4 .\n- Structure : Monolithe | Biome(s) : Anywhere during Infdev . | Description : These were chunk-sized patches of terrain that would generate up to the height limit. They were never intended to be in the game as they were just a glitch . Monoliths were patched in the version Alpha v1.2.0 Preview .", "type": "Document"}}